############################################################
## COMPREHENSIVE CLAIMS & ACCIDENTS GUIDANCE
############################################################

autoins:ClaimsAccidentsGuidance a owl:Class ;
  rdfs:label "Claims and Accidents Declaration Guidance" ;
  autoins:whyInsurerNeed "Insurers need specific details to: 1) Assign fault (liability), 2) Validate the claim credibility, 3) Assess value and repair method, 4) Determine policy coverage and exclusions." ;
  autoins:faultAssignment "Precise details help claims adjuster determine who was at fault. 'Hit stationary object' is clear fault. 'Damage from falling object' may be no-fault comprehensive claim." ;
  autoins:claimValidation "Specific story is more credible. Vague descriptions can be red flag for potential fraud." ;
  autoins:repairAssessment "Knowing exact cause helps assessors know what to look for and how best to repair damage." ;
  autoins:policyCoverage "Some policies have specific exclusions or conditions. Exact nature determines if incident is covered." ;
  autoins:descriptionPrinciple "Primary job is to describe incident and damage with precise detail to give insurer clear picture of event." .

